            <h3 id="compound-component-pattern" class="doc-h3">Compound Component Pattern</h3>
            <p class="doc-section-subtitle">The Split Button is a composite widget consisting of two focusable zones: the primary action button and the dropdown menu trigger (chevron). Each zone must be independently operable via keyboard and screen reader. The button part triggers the primary action, while the chevron part opens a dropdown menu of secondary actions.</p>
            <ul class="doc-list">
              <li>The Split Button should be treated as two adjacent but related controls, not a single button.</li>
              <li>Each part must be a native <code style="font-family:monospace;font-size:13px;padding:2px 8px;border-radius:6px;background:rgba(37,99,235,0.06);color:var(--prism-violet);">&lt;button&gt;</code> element to inherit default accessibility behaviors.</li>
              <li>The visual grouping (shared container, continuous background) communicates the relationship between the two parts.</li>
            </ul>
